[[File:City Theater, Tehran, Iran.jpg|thumb|City Theater, Tehran]] The '''City Theater''' ({{lang-fa|تئاتر شهر}}, ''Teātr-e Šahr'') is a [[performing arts]] complex in [[Tehran]], the capital of [[Iran]]. It was built with the initiative of [[Shahbanu]] [[Farah Pahlavi]] under the rule of [[Mohammad Reza Pahlavi]], the last [[Shah]] of Iran.
It contains several performance spaces including the halls of Charsou, Qashqai, Saye, and the main hall.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.teatreshahr.com/en/ |title=Tehran City Theater website |accessdate=June 27, 2012}}</ref> The complex was designed by architect Ali Sardar Afkhami in the 1960s,<ref>{{Citation |publisher = Routledge |isbn = 0415059283 |publication-place = London |author =Don Rubin, ed. |url = http://openlibrary.org/books/OL917814M/The_world_encyclopedia_of_contemporary_theatre |title = The World Encyclopedia of Contemporary Theatre |publication-date = 1998 |oclc = 32008932 |id = 0415059283 }}</ref> and opened in 1972. After the [[1979 Revolution]], the [[Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance (Iran)|Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance]] has overseen its operation.<ref>{{Citation |publisher = Routledge |isbn = 9780415260879 |title = World Encyclopedia of Contemporary Theatre: Asia/Pacific |url = http://openlibrary.org/books/OL7488911M/World_Encyclopedia_of_Contemporary_Theatre |author = Don Rubin et al., eds. |publication-date = 2001 |id = 0415260876 }}</ref>
