[[File:A Plunge into Space, cover image.jpg|thumb|upright|''A Plunge into Space'' by [[Robert Cromie]] (1890), a rare book in the Eaton Collection <ref>[http://scotty.ucr.edu/record=b2615895~S5  A Plunge Into Space], catalog record at UCR</ref>]]
'''The Eaton Collection of Science Fiction and Fantasy''', formerly known as the '''J. Lloyd Eaton Collection of Science Fiction, Fantasy, Horror, and Utopian Literature''',{{sfn|Swigart|2005|p=23}} is "the largest publicly accessible collection of [[science fiction]], [[fantasy fiction|fantasy]], [[horror fiction|horror]] and [[utopian fiction|utopian and dystopian literature]] in the world".<ref>{{cite news|author=[[Associated Press]] |url=http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2014/Apr/07/rare-book-from-1623-joins-uc-riverside-collection/ |title=Rare book from 1623 joins UC Riverside collection |newspaper=[[San Diego Union-Tribune]] |date=April 7, 2014 |accessdate=July 30, 2014}}</ref> It is housed in Special Collections and Archives of the UCR Libraries at the [[University of California, Riverside]].<ref name=collection/> It consists of more than 300,000 items, including [[hardcover]] and [[paperback]] books, SF [[fanzine]]s, film and visual material, and [[comic book]]s, including [[manga]] and [[anime]], as well as a variety of archival materials.<ref name=collection-about/>

==Eaton==
