'''Vale Tudo Japan (VTJ)''' is an annual [[mixed martial arts]] competition held in Japan. Arranged by promotor [[Satoru Sayama]], it ran from 1994 to 1999 with three reunion events in 2009, 2012 and 2016. A pair of tournaments were held in 1994 and '95, both of which were won by Brazilian jiu-jitsu legend [[Rickson Gracie]].
